# SRA - Smart Resource Allocation

Hackathon project by Taskforce 141. Data-driven volunteer coordination for social impact.

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 16 (App Router) + TypeScript
- Prisma 7 ORM with SQLite (dev) — requires `@prisma/adapter-better-sqlite3`
- NextAuth.js v5 beta (Credentials provider, JWT sessions)
- shadcn/ui v4 (base-ui/react based) + Tailwind CSS v4
- Recharts for charts
- PapaParse for CSV parsing
- DeepSeek API for AI severity analysis
- next-themes for dark/light mode

## Database (3 tables)

- **User** — admin (hardcoded) + volunteers (created by admin). Password hashed with bcryptjs. Role: "admin" | "volunteer". Skills/tags stored as JSON strings (SQLite compat).
- **Upload** — one per CSV file. Stores header schema as JSON, AI summary, severity stats. Status: uploading → parsing → analyzing → done | failed.
- **SurveyEntry** — one per CSV row. `rawData` is a JSON string of key-value pairs (normalized column headers). Severity 1-5, status: pending | resolved | no_action_needed.

## Architecture Rules

- Prisma client requires `PrismaBetterSqlite3` adapter — see `src/lib/prisma.ts`
- The dev.db file lives at the project root (not in prisma/), matching `DATABASE_URL="file:./dev.db"`
- Admin is seeded via `prisma/seed.ts` — never create admin through the API
- Auth guards: dashboard layout checks session server-side, API routes check `await auth()`
- Role guards: admin-only endpoints check `session.user.role === "admin"`
- CSV upload flow: parse → store entries → fire-and-forget `analyzeUpload()` → frontend polls status

## UI/Styling Rules

- shadcn v4 uses base-ui/react. Button does NOT support `asChild`. Use `render` prop for polymorphism: `<Button render={<Link href="..." />}>`
- DialogTrigger also does NOT support `asChild` — style it directly with className
- ALWAYS use theme-aware CSS variables: `bg-card`, `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-primary`, `text-primary`, etc.
- NEVER hardcode colors like `bg-white`, `bg-slate-xxx`, `text-gray-xxx`
- All Card components must have `border border-border` for visible borders in both themes
- Dark mode variants: use `dark:` prefix, e.g. `bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-950/30`

## File Patterns

- API routes: `src/app/api/` — return NextResponse.json
- Pages: `src/app/` — server components by default, "use client" when needed
- Shared components: `src/components/`
- Utilities: `src/lib/` (prisma.ts, auth.ts, csv-parser.ts, ai-analyzer.ts)
- Types: `src/types/index.ts`
